🔹 What the System Does
VaultForge‑Live enables creators to:

Anchor their work in real time

Establish first‑to‑market presence

Generate a timestamped public record

Maintain private protection for the underlying work

Prepare for future buildout, licensing, and investment

The system uses a dual‑vault model:

Layer	Purpose
Private Vault	Protected creation, trade‑secret preservation, continuity chain, relic generation
Public Vault	Forward‑facing metadata, public timestamping, first‑to‑market anchoring
This ensures creators can safely share what the world needs to see while keeping their core work protected.

🔹 How It Works (Public‑Safe Explanation)
Creators add their work to the private vault  
This protects the underlying material as a trade secret and anchors it in the continuity chain.

Creators publish a title + description to the public vault  
This establishes first‑to‑market status and creates a public timestamp.

The system automatically generates a public‑safe relic entry  
This shows that the work exists and is protected, without revealing the protected content.

Creators can continue building privately  
The private vault maintains continuity, evolution, and authorship integrity.

Optional monthly services  
Creators can access indexing, blueprinting, and investment‑readiness workflows.

